uss the formation of their new investment business rubenstein who was a washingtonbased lawyer had worked in the carter administration norris and daneillo had previously worked together at marriott corporation while conway was a finance executive at mci communications of the founding five partners rubenstein conway and daneillo remain active in the business while rosenbaum left in the first year and norris departed in  carlyle was founded with  million of financial backing from t rowe price alex brown  sons first interstate equities and the richard king mellon family in the late s carlyle raised capital on a dealbydeal basis to pursue leveraged buyout investments including a failed takeover battle for chichis the firm raised its first dedicated buyout fund with  million of investor commitments in  in its early years carlyle also advised in transactions including a  million investment by prince alwaleed bin talal a member of the saudi royal family in citigroup in  the crusader weapon system developed by united defense carlyles largest investment in the defense industry was cancelled in may  carlyle initially developed a reputation for acquiring businesses related to the defense industry in  carlyle completed the acquisition of the electronics division of general dynamics corporation renamed gde systems a producer of military electronics systems carlyle would later sell the business to tracor in october  carlyle acquired magnavox electronic systems the military communications and electronicwarfare systems segment of magnavox from philips electronics in  carlyle sold magnavox for approximately  million to hughes aircraft company in  carlyle also invested in vought aircraft through a partnership with northrop grumman carlyles most notable defense industry investment came in october  with its acquisition of united defense industries the  million acquisition of united defense represented carlyles largest investment to that point carlyle was able to complete an ipo of united defense on the new york stock exchange in december  selling a significant portion of its interest in the company carlyle completed a sale of its remaining united defense stock and exited the investment in april  in more recent years carlyle has deemphasized its focus on defense industry investments carlyles  investor conference took place on september   in the weeks following the meeting it was reported that shafiq bin laden a member of the bin laden family had been the guest of honor and that they were investors in carlyle managed funds later reports confirmed that the bin laden family had invested  million into carlyles  billion carlyle partners ii fund in  making the family relatively small investors with the firm however their overall investment might have been considerably larger with the  million committed in  only being an initial contribution that grew over time these connections would later be profiled in michael moores fahrenheit  the bin laden family liquidated its holdings in carlyles funds in october  just after the september th attacks when the connection of their family name to the carlyle groups name became impolitic –edit the carlyle group logo following the collapse of the dotcom bubble in  and  buyout activity declined significantly marked by the twostage buyout of dex media at the end of  and  large multibilliondollar us buyouts could once again obtain significant high yield debt financing and larger transactions could be completed carlyle together with welsh carson anderson  stowe led a  billion buyout of qwestdex the buyout was the third largest corporate buyout since  qwestdexs purchase occurred in two stages a  billion acquisition of assets known as dex media east in november  and a  billion acquisition of assets known as dex media west in  r h donnelley corporation acquired dex media in  shortly after dex media other larger buyouts would be completed signaling the resurgence in private equity was underway lou gerstner former chairman and 