es across  offices in north america south america europe the middle east africa asia and australia over the course of two decades carlyle has amassed a portfolio of  billion in assets under management across  funds and  fund of fund vehicles and has made investments in more than  companies and more than  real estate investments in  carlyle completed a  million initial public offering and began trading on the nasdaq stock exchange on may   according to a  ranking called the pei  based on capital raised over the last five years carlyle was ranked no  as the largest private equity firm in the world contents  business segments  corporate private equity  real assets  global market strategies  investment solutions  history  founding and early history  –  since   ownership changes  subsidiaries and jointventures  carlyle capital corporation  in documentaries  notable employees and advisors  business  politicians  media  see also  references  notes and references  external links business segmentsedit the firm is organized into four business segments corporate private equity – management of carlyles family of private equity funds investing primarily in leveraged buyout and growth capital transactions through a range of geographically focused investment funds real assets – management of carlyles family of energy and real estate investment funds focusing on the us europe and asia global market strategies – management of various credit equities and hedge fund vehicles with over  billion in assets under management and investment solutions – management of three investment groups corporate private equity real estate and liquid market solutions which invest in primary secondary and coinvestments commingled funds and separately managed accounts corporate private equityedit carlyles corporate private equity division manages a series of leveraged buyout and growth capital investment funds with specific geographic or industry focuses carlyle invests primarily in the following industries aerospace defense  government services consumer  retail energy financial services health care industrial real estate technology and business services telecommunications  media and transportation as of december   carlyle managed  active funds with  billion in assets under management consisting of buyout funds – carlyle manages a group of  active funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   growth capital funds – carlyle manages  active growth capital funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   real assetsedit carlyles real assets division manages  active investment funds focused on real estate infrastructure and energy and natural resources the real assets business has two primary areas of focus real estate funds – carlyle manages  active real estate funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   energy natural resources  carlyle manages eight funds advised by carlyle energy affiliate ngp energy capital management with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   two power funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   and one international energy fund with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   global market strategiesedit carlyles global market strategies division manages  investment across a range of investments including credit emerging markets macroeconomic strategies commodities trading leveraged loans structured credit and mezzanine debt as of december   the global market strategies division had  billion of assets under management across several strategies structured credit funds – carlyle manages  investment funds including clos with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   distressed and corporate opportunities – carlyle manages  funds focused on investments in distressed debt with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   mezzanine – carlyle manages  funds focused on mezzanine debt investments in middle market companies with approximately  million in assets under management as of december   carlyle also manages a fund focused on mezzanine debt investments in energy and power projects in north america with  billion of assets under management as of december   long  short credit – carlyle’s claren road asset management subsidiary manages two hedge funds focused on credit investments with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   emerging markets and macroeconomic strategies – carlyles emerging sovereign group subsidiary manages  hedge funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   commodities – carlyles vermillion subsidiary manages  investment funds with approximately  billion in assets under management as of december   investment solutionsedit alpinvest partners type private industry private equity headquarters amsterdam netherlands products fund investments secondaries coinvestments mezzanine total assets us  billion website wwwalpinvestcom main article alpinvest partners alpinvest partners is one of the largest private equity investment managers globally with over  billion under management as of march   invested alongside more than  private equity firms founded in  alpinvest has historically been the exclusive manager of private equity investments for the investment managers of two of the worlds largest pension funds stichting pensioenfonds abp abp and stichting pensioenfonds zorg en welzijn pfzw both based in the netherlands in  carlyle acquired alpinvest and has integrated the business including its leading fundoffunds and secondary platforms significantly expanding carlyles global asset management business alpinvest pursues investment opportunities across the entire spectrum of private equity including large buyout middlemarket buyout venture capital growth capital mezzanine distressed and sustainable energy investments alpinvest has offices in new york city amsterdam and hong kong with over  investment professionals and over  employees carlyles real estate fund of funds group is called metropolitan which provides investors with access to multimanager real estate funds and solutions with more than  fund managers in the united states europe asia and latin america metropolitan constructs and manages us nonus and global real estate portfolios which include primary and secondary fund interests as well as coinvestments dgam is carlyles liquid solutions team dgam provides investors access to an array of proprietary and thirdparty hedge funds around the world dgam works to manage the complexities of alternative asset classes with a complementary blend of investment and operations expertise historyedit history of private equity and venture capital early history origins of modern private equity the s leveraged buyout boom the s leveraged buyout and the venture capital bubble the s dotcom bubble to the credit crunch v t e founding and early historyedit carlyle was founded in  as an investment banking boutique by five original partners with backgrounds in finance and government william e conway jr stephen l norris david m rubenstein daniel a daniello and greg rosenbaum the founding partners named the firm after the carlyle hotel in new york city where norris and rubenstein had often met to discuss the formation of their new investment business rubenstein who was a washingtonbased lawyer had worked in the carter administration norris and daneillo had previously worked together at marriott corporation while conway was a finance executive at mci communications of the founding five partners rubenstein conway and daneillo remain active in the business while rosenbaum left in the first year and norris departed in  carlyle was founded with  million of financial backing from t rowe price alex brown  sons first interstate equities and the richard king mellon family in the late s carlyle raised capital on a dealbydeal basis to pursue leveraged buyout investments including a failed takeover battle for chichis the firm raised its first dedicated buyout fund with  million of investor commitments in  in its early years carlyle also advised in transactions including a  million investment by prince alwaleed bin talal a member of the saudi royal family in citigroup in  the crusader weapon system developed by united defense carlyles largest investment in the defense industry was cancelled in may  carlyle initially developed a reputation for acquiring businesses related to the defense industry in  carlyle completed the acquisition of the electronics division of general dynamics corporation renamed gde systems a producer of military electronics systems carlyle would later sell the business to tracor in october  carlyle acquired magnavox electronic systems the military communications and electronicwarfare systems segment of magnavox from philips electronics in  carlyle sold magnavox for approximately  million to hughes aircraft company in  carlyle also invested in vought aircraft through a partnership with northrop grumman carlyles most notable defense industry investment came in october  with its acquisition of united defense industries the  million acquisition of united defense represented carlyles largest investment to that point carlyle was able to complete an ipo of united defense on the new york stock exchange in december  selling a significant portion of its interest in the company carlyle completed a sale of its remaining united defense stock and exited the investment in april  in more recent years carlyle has deemphasized its focus on defense industry investments carlyles  investor conference took place on september   in the weeks following the meeting it was reported that shafiq bin laden a member of the bin laden family had been the guest of honor and that they were investors in carlyle managed funds later reports confirmed that the bin laden family had invested  million into carlyles  billion carlyle partners ii fund in  making the family relatively small investors with the firm however their overall investment might have been considerably larger with the  million committed in  only being an initial contribution that grew over time these connections would later be profiled in michael moores fahrenheit  the bin laden family liquidated its holdings in carlyles funds in october  just after the september th attacks when the connection of their family name to the carlyle groups name became impolitic –edit the carlyle group logo following the collapse of the dotcom bubble in  and  buyout activity declined significantly marked by the twostage buyout of dex media at the end of  and  large multibilliondollar us buyouts could once again obtain significant high yield debt financing and larger transactions could be completed carlyle together with welsh carson anderson  stowe led a  billion buyout of qwestdex the buyout was the third largest corporate buyout since  qwestdexs purchase occurred in two stages a  billion acquisition of assets known as dex media east in november  and a  billion acquisition of assets known as dex media west in  r h donnelley corporation acquired dex media in  shortly after dex media other larger buyouts would be completed signaling the resurgence in private equity was underway lou gerstner former chairman and ceo of ibm and nabisco was appointed chairman of carlyle in january  replacing frank carlucci gerstner would serve in that position through october  the hiring of gerstner was intended to reduce the perception of carlyle as a politically dominated firm at the time carlyle which had been founded  years earlier had accumulated  billion of assets under management and had generated annualized returns for investors of  carlyle also announced the  billion acquisition of hawaiian telcom from verizon in may  carlyles investment was immediately challenged when hawaii regulators delayed the closing of the buyout the company also suffered billing and customerservice issues as it had to recreate its backoffice systems hawaiian telcom ultimately filed for bankruptcy in december  costing carlyle the  million it had invested in the company carlyle led the  billion buyout of hertz in  as the activity of the large private equity firms increased in the mids carlyle kept pace with such competitors as kohlberg kravis roberts blackstone group and tpg capital in  carlyle together with clayton dubilier  rice and merrill lynch completed the  billion leveraged buyout of the hertz corporation the largest car rental agency from ford the following year in august  carlyle and its riverstone holdings affiliate partnered with goldman sachs capital partners in the  billion including assumed debt acquisition of kinder morgan one of the largest pipeline operators in the us the buyout was backed by richard kinder the companys cofounder and a former president of enron in september  carlyle led a consortium comprising blackstone group permira and tpg capital in the  billion takeover of freescale semiconductor at the time of its announcement freescale would be the largest leveraged buyout of a technology company ever surpassing the  buyout of sungard the buyers were forced to pay an extra  million because kkr made a lastminute bid as the original deal was about to be signed shortly after the deal closed in late  cell phone sales at motorola corp freescales former corporate parent and a major customer began dropping sharply in addition in the recession of – freescales chip sales to automakers fell off and the company came under great financial strain earlier that year in january  carlyle together with blackstone group alpinvest partners hellman  friedman kohlberg kravis roberts and thomas h lee partners acquired nielsen company the global information and media company formerly known as vnu in an  billion buyout also in  carlyle acquired oriental trading company which ultimately declared bankruptcy in august  as well as forba dental management the owner of small smiles dental centers the largest us chain of dental clinics for children since edit david rubenstein the head of the carlyle group the largest private equity firm by investor commitments during the – buyout boom on january   the carlyle group purchased synagro technologies a municipal sludge hauler and spreader for  per share carlyle continued to make large investments into  as the buyout market reached its peak in june  carlyle agrees to acquire hd supply for  billion along with bain capital and clayton dubilier  rice with each agreeing to buy a onethird stake in the division home depot sold their wholesale construction supply business to fund a stock repurchase estimated at  billion also in june  carlyle announced that it would partner with onex corporation to buy the allison transmission unit from general motors for  billion on december   david rubenstein representing the carlyle group purchased the magna carta one of seventeen copies at sothebys auction house in new york city he paid the perot foundation  million mr rubenstein expressed his intent for it to be returned to the national archives for display on may   booz allen hamilton announced that it would sell a majority stake in the us government business to the carlyle group for  billion the transaction was expected to be complete july   in november  the carlyle group was named private equity firm of the year in the us at the financial timesmergermarket  ma awards in march  new york state and federal authorities began an investigation into payments made by carlyles riverstone holdings subsidiary to placement agents allegedly made in exchange for investments from the new york state common retirement system the states pension fund in  carlyle had entered into a joint venture with riverstone holdings an energy and power focused private equity firm founded by pierre f lapeyre jr and david m leuschen it was alleged that these payments were in fact bribes or kickbacks made to pension officials who have been under investigation by new york state attorney general andrew cuomo in may  carlyle agreed to pay  million in a settlement with cuomo and accepted changes to its fundraising practices on october   carlyle group bought metaldyne – a global automotive components supplier on november   david rosendall a synagro executive was sentenced for conspiring to commit bribery in the corruption scandal which eventually brought down the mayor of the city of detroit the executive for the carlyle subsidiary was caught giving cash to detroit city leadership on september   carlyle group announced the completed acquisition of nutritional supplement manufacturer nbty for  billion on september   the carpet manufacturer brintons announced that it had been acquired by the carlyle group on october   the pharmaceutical contract research organisation ppd announced that it had been acquired by the carlyle group in august  carlyle group announced that it would purchase dupont performance coatings dpc for  billion in cash dpc is a global supplier of vehicle and industrial coating systems the transaction closed in the first quarter of  and the new company was named axalta coating systems in october  carlyle group sold its remaining  stake in housing development finance corporation for around  million in november  the carlyle group unveiled the first investment of its new subsaharan african fund carlyle is part of a small group of investors that will inject  million into export trading group a tanzaniabased agricultural company that sources commodities from africas small farmers and sells those goods to china india and elsewhere january  carlyle group began talks to sell synagro after plowing over  in  to keep the entity afloat april   carlyle groups subsidiary synagro technologies filed for chapter  bankruptcy and in lieu of sale a reorganization and sale of the company to an affiliate of swedish privateequity firm eqt the offer price was set at  mill